  <prompt>
    `AnalysisActionService` currently reads an Action and projects an `ActionType` value derived from
    `sprk_analysisaction.sprk_actiontypeid → sprk_analysisactiontype.sprk_executoractiontype`. Post-task 024, the
    orchestrator no longer consumes that value (dispatch comes from `node.sprk_executortype`). This task removes
    the projection from the Action read path so the service returns Action data without the dispatch derivative.
    The Dataverse field DROP itself happens in Wave 4 (task 043/044) — this task just stops READING it.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer. Simplification of a service read method.
    Discipline: stop reading the dispatch-derived field; leave the column in Dataverse for Wave 4 to drop.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `AnalysisActionService.GetActionAsync` (or equivalent read method) no longer reads or projects:
    - `sprk_actiontypeid` lookup
    - `sprk_executoractiontype` INT
    The returned Action shape no longer contains an `ActionType` (or `ExecutorType`) field — those are now node-level concerns.
    Action DTO simplifies to: prompt template + output schema + temperature (plus identity).
    Build + tests pass.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="service">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisActionService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="orchestrator">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs</file>
